ext":"(M, * Meyd, TA.) One says, (M, Meyd, TA,) i. e. a rájiz says, addressing a camel belonging to him, (Har p. 642,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_in~aka laA ta$okuw A_ilaY muSam~iti\n                      \n                     \n                        faA@Sobiro EalaY AlHimoli Alv~aqiyli A^awo muti"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thou complainest not to one who cares for thy complaint; therefore endure with patience the bearing of the heavy burden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"die"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, Meyd, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$okuw A_ilaY gayori muSam~itK","text_ar":"تَشْكُو اـِلَى غَيْرِ مُصَمِّتٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou complainest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to one who cares not for thy case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a proverb. (Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Meyd","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}